corridor()        UNKNOWN SECTION OF THE MANUAL        corridor()



     would take in this landscape.

CAVEATS
     This program does not abide by the nice map data  resampling
     and masking conventions of GRASS.  In particular:

     No mask -
          The input and output files are not masked.

     No resampling -
          The input map are not resampled to the current  window.
          The  output map will cover exactly the same area as the
          input map.

     Square cells -
          The grid-cells of the input map must be square.







































